We recently took a 4-day trip from Mumbai to Phuket with our 12-month-old daughter, and it was such a beautiful experience! ✈️🌴 Traveling with a baby can feel overwhelming, but keeping a few things in mind made our journey smooth and enjoyable:
	1.	Took a direct flight to avoid long layovers
	2.	Carried all essential medicines for Rubani
	3.	Stayed at one hotel throughout the trip for stability
	4.	Chose a hotel with a kitchen to cook meals suited for her
	5.	Explored nearby tourist spots to avoid long travel
	6.	Stepped out mostly in the evenings to beat the heat or visited indoor/AC places
	7.	Always kept food & milk handy while on the go
	8.	Reached the airport early and made sure her tummy was full before the flight

That’s it! 😊 Traveling with a baby doesn’t have to be hard — just plan a little and go with the flow. You and your baby will absolutely love the memories you make 💛

Follow us for more family travel tips!

With love,
Rupal & Karan ✨

latestPosts.caption:
Happy Birthday Maa

Today you would have turned 59 years old. Wish we were celebrating this together. Being with you on your birthday was something that made me happy. No matter how far you have gone I will always wish you on this day and miss you a little more. 

I would like to share few qualities of my mom with you all on her 59th birthday. 
1. She was a wonderful cook and yummiest were her cakes and puddings. Some of my favourite was her black forest cake and biscuit pudding. Just too yummy 😋 
2. She was the life or our family, she always made sure everyone in the family is happy and she would crack jokes that you will die laughing on. 
3. She was a typical indian mother who would do anything and everything for her kids. Her life was in her kids. 

Happy birthday once again mom, I am sure you are spreading smiles in heaven and making everyone laugh and laugh. 
Love you ❤️
